        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced\u00a0chorizo</strong> and cook for 3 min or until it begins to crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-creamy-chorizo-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chorizo is cooking, add the <strong>gnocchi</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the gnocchi for 3 min or until it begins to rise to the top of the pot</p><p>Once done, drain the gnocchi, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy cooking water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-creamy-chorizo-gnocchi-with-spinach/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>roasted\u00a0garlic paste</strong>\u00a0to the pan and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add 100ml\u00a0<span class=\"text-danger\">[175ml]</span><strong>\u00a0boiled water</strong>\u00a0and the\u00a0<strong>soft cheese</strong>\u00a0and give everything a good mix up</p>",
